AGI -&nbsp;"Improprio, irrational, aimed at judiciary and malicious conformism because &nbsp; slows down justice even more". The president of the Milan Tribunal Fabio Roia >boccia in an interview with AGI the measure with which the government introduces, starting from 2026, the psycho-active test for the magistrates.
&nbsp;
"As a first step, it is an initiative that goes contrary to the objectives of the Pnrr, among which there is the speeding up of the system. The tests will slow down the contests and recruitment procedures of new magistrates. In Milan, 60 judges are missing, there is therefore a 20 percent broom and 41 percent of administrative staff. The tests will not help to fill this deficiency > making it more complicated also to dispose of arrears".
&nbsp;
"In the merits I find that where these tests have been applied, as in France, the objectives have not been achieved. The risk is that they certify a judicial conformity that we do not need. On the contrary: now more than ever in a perspective of interpretation of transnational norms, we need courage from the magistrates." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Roia states that "the requirements of balance, independence and impartiality" are already active and functional.
&nbsp;
" Balance control is important also because &nbsp; our work is becoming increasingly wearable even in the light of the demand for productivity under poor organic conditions. The future magistrates are already 'tested' during the internship and in the six months before taking possession of the function and then, when they become, every 4 years. A verification that is necessary to progress in the career. To assess their balance, are the presidents of the courts and sections, the judicial council, the Csm. If a judge, for example, is suffering from psychiatric pathology >o is in the situation, as sometimes happens, not to deposit the reasons for his decisions for a blockade, the procedure of the dispensation takes place. In addition, a recent law states that a magistrate no longer able to carry out its duties is moved to public administration, obviously without decision-making." For the head of the Milanese judges, "this measure seems like a kind of mistrust that we do not deserve that it launches a distorted image of the togae".
&nbsp;
"The absence of balance is confused with an unwelcome decision. We also have our demerits but in a proper team game in a country system institutions should not be distrusted among themselves, for the sake of citizens." &nbsp;
&nbsp;

